President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Debra Satz as a member of the National Council on the Humanities. Satz is currently a professor at Stanford University and has held various positions in the field of ethics and philosophy.

Additionally, Stuart Symington has been nominated as the Ambassador to the Federal Republic of Nigeria. Symington is a career member of the Foreign Service and has served in various diplomatic roles, including as the U.S. Ambassador to Rwanda and Djibouti.

Lastly, Kody Kinsley has been appointed as the Assistant Secretary for Management at the Department of the Treasury. Kinsley has experience in policy and program support, previously serving in the District of Columbia Department of Human Services and the Department of the Treasury.

President Obama expressed his honor in having these individuals serve the country and highlighted their experience and expertise.